.TH "RALPHGLASSES" "1" "Apr 2026" "ralphglasses" ""

.SH NAME
ralphglasses-doctor - Check required tools and environment


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBralphglasses doctor [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Verify that all required binaries are installed and the environment is
configured correctly for running ralphglasses.

.PP
Checks include:
  - Provider binaries (claude, gemini, codex)
  - Git binary and version (>= 2.20 for worktree support)
  - Config file (~/.ralphglasses/config.json when HOME is available; otherwise the XDG config dir)
  - State directory (~/.ralphglasses when HOME is available; otherwise the XDG state dir) permissions
  - SQLite store (~/.ralphglasses/state.db when HOME is available; otherwise the XDG state dir)
  - Scan path validity and repo discovery
  - Disk space availability
  - API keys (ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, GEMINI_API_KEY, OPENAI_API_KEY)

.PP
Exit code 0 if all checks pass (warnings are OK), exit code 1 if any fail.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for doctor

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=false]
	Output results as JSON


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable verbose debug logging to stderr

.PP
\fB--http-addr\fP=""
	Enable health endpoints on this address (e.g. :9090, disabled by default)

.PP
\fB--log-format\fP="json"
	Log format (json, text)

.PP
\fB--log-level\fP="info"
	Log level (debug, info, warn, error)

.PP
\fB--scan-path\fP="~/hairglasses-studio"
	Root directory to scan for ralph-enabled repos

.PP
\fB--scan-timeout\fP="30s"
	Timeout for repository scanning (e.g. 30s, 1m)

.PP
\fB--web-addr\fP=""
	Enable web UI on this address (e.g. :8080, disabled by default). Set RALPHGLASSES_WEB_TOKEN for auth.


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Run all checks
  ralphglasses doctor

  # Machine-readable JSON output
  ralphglasses doctor --json

  # Run with debug output
  ralphglasses doctor --debug
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBralphglasses(1)\fP


